<P class=MsoNormal><B><SPAN
style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></B></P>
<P class=MsoNormal><B><SPAN
style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">Duty Hours:<SPAN
style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN></SPAN></B><SPAN
style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">The Secretary&#8217;s Command
Center (SCC) will be operational 24/7 and will be staffed by a minimum of one
officer at all times.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>The shifts
will be assigned based on the needs of the SCC.</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal>&nbsp;<B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">Deputy Director, Secretary's Command
Center<U><o:p></o:p></U></SPAN></B></P>
<H5>PHS 0-5/6 billet</H5>
<P class=MsoNormal><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><U><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">During response
operations</SPAN></U></B><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">, the
incumbent of this position will be assigned to assist the SCC Director in the
management of the SCC that facilitates the activation of the NDMS to deploy to
the field to render health and medical assistance as needed during special
events, disasters, major transportation accidents and other activities requiring
team deployment. The incumbent assists the SCC Director in the communication and
information gathering and distribution and serve as the point of contact with
the field until the SERT is operational in the field and able to take provide
reports from the field.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>The SCC
will assume a support roll to ensure that all requests for national-level
guidance are met, required personnel and equipment are available, and that HHS
leadership is appropriately briefed on response activities.
<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>
<H1><U><SPAN
style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-size: 16.0pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial">MAJOR
DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES</SPAN></U>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></H1>
<P class=a
style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0in; TEXT-INDENT: 0in; TEXT-ALIGN: justify; tab-stops: -1.0in 0in"><B
style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><U>During periods of readiness</U></B>, the
incumbent is responsible to the SCC Director.<SPAN
style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>He/she shall assist the SCC Director to
ensure that the SCC is in a continual state of readiness for activation. This
includes maintaining a cadre of highly skilled SCC personnel.<SPAN
style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>The incumbent shall support and
participate in the process to identify, develop, coordinate, and implement
training that addresses SCC related issues, including but not limited to issues
raised in After Action Reports. He/she shall assist in the analyzing and
implementation of technology that enhances the SCC function.<SPAN
style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>The incumbent will be required to work
an irregular work shift to provide readiness coverage of the SCC.<SPAN
style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>In the absence of the SCC Director the
incumbent shall execute the duties of the SCC Director required to maintain the
SCC in a continual state of readiness for activation. Listed below are the
duties and responsibilities associated with maintaining the EOC in the proper
state of readiness.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>The incumbent
shall support and assist the SCC Director to ensure that the listed readiness
responsibilities are executed in a prompt and proficient manner:</P>
<P class=MsoNormal><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'"><SPAN
style="mso-spacerun: yes"></SPAN><o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal
style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0.5in; TEXT-INDENT: -0.5in; mso-list: l9 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: -1.0in 0in list .5in"><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">1.<SPAN
style="FONT: 7pt 'Times New Roman'">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</SPAN></SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">Responsible for
recruiting and maintaining a cadre of highly skilled SCC personnel that are
available, as needed, to work in the SCC when activated.<SPAN
style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Interviews candidates and selects staff
for positions in the SCC.</SPAN><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal
style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0.5in; TEXT-INDENT: -0.5in; mso-list: l9 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: -1.0in 0in list .5in"><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">2.<SPAN
style="FONT: 7pt 'Times New Roman'">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</SPAN></SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">Represents the SCC in
dealings with internal as well as other Federal, State and local entities.<SPAN
style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Promote and maintain effective working
relationships with the various organizations.</SPAN></P>
<P class=a style="mso-list: l9 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list .5in">3.<SPAN
style="FONT: 7pt 'Times New Roman'">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</SPAN>Develops, documents, and delivers monthly training for all SCC personnel.
Training includes:</P>
<P class=MsoNormal><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">&nbsp;</SPAN><I
style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal"><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">Overview and Update &#8211;</SPAN></I><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'"> Provides the big picture of where the
SCC fits into the HHS response to stand-by events, emergencies and
disasters.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Also provides
participants with an overview of recent changes.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'"><o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoBodyTextIndent><I style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal">Processes and
Technology</I> &#8211; Provides in-depth explanations of the processes and tools used
to perform SCC tasks. Training will be hands-on whenever possible.</P>
<P class=MsoNormal><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'"></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoBodyTextIndent><I style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal">Exercise</I> &#8211;
Designed to practice the processes and technologies taught.<SPAN
style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Exercise will be coached as needed.</P>
<P class=MsoBodyTextIndent><I style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal"><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">Review &#8211; </SPAN></I><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">An opportunity for participants to rate
the effectiveness of the training and suggest topics/methodologies for future
training.</SPAN><I style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal"><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></I></P>
<P class=MsoNormal
style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0.5in; TEXT-INDENT: -0.5in; mso-list: l9 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: -1.0in 0in list .5in"><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">4.<SPAN
style="FONT: 7pt 'Times New Roman'">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</SPAN></SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">Compiles After Action
Reports following all activations of the SCC to identify all issues and/or
suggestions that would increase SCC effectiveness.<SPAN
style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Develops, documents, implements, and
trains to correct issues identified in After Action
Reports.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="tab-stops: -1.0in 0in"><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">&nbsp;</SPAN><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">5.<SPAN
style="FONT: 7pt 'Times New Roman'">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</SPAN></SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">Convenes working
groups of necessary personnel and other agency personnel, as required, to
address issues of policy and procedure that would increase the SCC's
effectiveness in support of disaster response efforts.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="tab-stops: -1.0in 0in"><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">&nbsp;</SPAN><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">6.<SPAN
style="FONT: 7pt 'Times New Roman'">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</SPAN></SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">Analyzes trends in
technology and products that may be adapted for use in the SCC.<SPAN
style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Must be able to analyze a product to
ensure it interacts seamlessly with existing technology, significantly
contributes to SCC operations, and is capable of being successfully operated by
intermittent users.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="tab-stops: -1.0in 0in"><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'"><o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal
style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0.5in; TEXT-INDENT: -0.5in; mso-list: l9 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: -1.0in 0in list .5in"><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">7.<SPAN
style="FONT: 7pt 'Times New Roman'">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</SPAN></SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">Designs, implements,
documents, trains, and maintains database applications such as an incident log,
personnel tracking, etc. to support SCC operations.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="tab-stops: -1.0in 0in"><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'"><o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal
style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0.5in; TEXT-INDENT: -0.5in; mso-list: l9 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: -1.0in 0in list .5in"><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">8.<SPAN
style="FONT: 7pt 'Times New Roman'">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</SPAN></SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">Ensures the
operational readiness of all equipment used to support SCC
operations.&nbsp;</SPAN><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal
style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0.5in; TEXT-INDENT: -0.5in; mso-list: l9 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: -1.0in 0in list .5in"><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">9.<SPAN
style="FONT: 7pt 'Times New Roman'">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</SPAN></SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">Independently
proposes or acts on management considerations relative to the development of
procedures for the SCC personnel; revises or changes the emphasis of existing
procedures, or terminates existing procedures as a result of policy
changes.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Deals effectively with
other EOCs on matters within their areas of responsibility.</SPAN><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal
style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0.5in; TEXT-INDENT: -0.5in; mso-list: l9 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: -1.0in 0in list .5in"><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">10.<SPAN
style="FONT: 7pt 'Times New Roman'">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</SPAN></SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">Independently
provides technical advice to external organizations and/or groups representing
the SCC's interest on program matters involving EOC policy and
procedures.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="tab-stops: -1.0in 0in"><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'"><o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal
style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0.5in; TEXT-INDENT: -0.5in; mso-list: l9 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: -1.0in 0in list .5in"><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">11.<SPAN
style="FONT: 7pt 'Times New Roman'">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</SPAN></SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">Establishes and
implements administrative policies, plans, and operational procedures that
support SCC operational capabilities.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="tab-stops: -1.0in 0in"><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'"><o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal
style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0.5in; TEXT-INDENT: -0.5in; mso-list: l9 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: -1.0in 0in list .5in"><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">12.<SPAN
style="FONT: 7pt 'Times New Roman'">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</SPAN></SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">Reviews response
manuals, plans, and other written materials relating to national emergency
preparedness and response to disasters of our partner agencies.<SPAN
style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Integrates concepts into current SCC
operations to eliminate duplication of effort and compatibility with other
partner agencies to ensure that optimal information flow is established and
maintained. <o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="tab-stops: -1.0in 0in"><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'"><o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><U><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">During response
operations</SPAN></U></B><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">, the
incumbent is responsible to the SCC Director.<SPAN
style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>He/she <o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">shall assist the
SCC Director in the management of all activities necessary to provide support to
a wide range of Federal health and medical resources being used during a
disaster. He/she shall support the management of the day-to-day operations of
the SCC.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>The incumbent shall be
required to work altered and extends shifts during response operations and SCC
activations, (including nights, weekends and holidays).<SPAN
style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>The incumbent shall work closely with
and support the SCC Director in the multifaceted aspects of SCC activation.<SPAN
style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>The incumbent shall work in the SCC and
maintain a continuum of management and operations in the absence of the SCC
Director.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Listed below are the
duties and responsibilities associated with an EOC activation.<SPAN
style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>The incumbent shall support and assist
the SCC Director to ensure proper and proficient execution of the following
duties and responsibilities: <o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>
<P class=a
style="mso-list: l10 level1 lfo11; tab-stops: -1.0in 0in list .5in">1.<SPAN
style="FONT: 7pt 'Times New Roman'">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</SPAN>Ensures that the SCC organization and operations are appropriate to
effectively support response operations.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
</SPAN>Coordinates the activation and deployment of all resources to the
incident scene.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal
style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0.5in; TEXT-INDENT: -0.5in; mso-list: l10 level1 lfo11; tab-stops: -1.0in 0in list .5in"><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">2.<SPAN
style="FONT: 7pt 'Times New Roman'">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</SPAN></SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">Provides general
guidance and supervision of the work of SCC staff to assure that they are
trained and provided with the equipment, supplies, support, etc., necessary to
satisfactorily carry out their assignments and activities.<SPAN
style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Establishes appropriate staffing levels
in the SCC to effectively support response operations.<SPAN
style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Staff may range from 3-30+ during
activations and may extend for several months.<SPAN
style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Exercises a high degree of judgement and
professional leadership in coordinating all activities of the SCC and guiding
the staff in solving difficult problems.</SPAN><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal
style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0.5in; TEXT-INDENT: -0.5in; mso-list: l10 level1 lfo11; tab-stops: -1.0in 0in list .5in"><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">3.<SPAN
style="FONT: 7pt 'Times New Roman'">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</SPAN></SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">Plans and assigns
work; sets goals and establishes priorities; evaluates performance of
subordinates; identifies training needs during activations; hears staff
complaints and takes appropriate action as necessary.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'"><o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal
style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0.5in; TEXT-INDENT: -0.5in; mso-list: l10 level1 lfo11; tab-stops: -1.0in 0in list .5in"><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">4.<SPAN
style="FONT: 7pt 'Times New Roman'">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</SPAN></SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">Keeps the various
agencies of jurisdiction informed on all matters affecting the effective
utilization of health and medical assets;</SPAN><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal
style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0.5in; TEXT-INDENT: -0.5in; mso-list: l10 level1 lfo11; tab-stops: -1.0in 0in list .5in"><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">5.<SPAN
style="FONT: 7pt 'Times New Roman'">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</SPAN></SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">Ensures that
multi-agency or inter-agency coordination is accomplished effectively within the
SCC; develops current and accurate assessments of the disaster situation, PHS
response activities, and the preparation of informational summaries; reviews all
written reports and communications prior to submission to the Assistant
Secretary and the Secretary; keeps HHS administration informed on all matters
regarding the response activities; and keeps HHS liaison officers assigned to
other agency operations centers current on response
operations.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="tab-stops: -1.0in 0in"><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">&nbsp;</SPAN><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">6.<SPAN
style="FONT: 7pt 'Times New Roman'">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</SPAN></SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">Participates in a
daily briefing with all deployed teams to maintain current information from the
resources assigned.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="tab-stops: -1.0in 0in"><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">&nbsp;</SPAN><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">7.<SPAN
style="FONT: 7pt 'Times New Roman'">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</SPAN></SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">Performs other
related duties as required, including tasks normally performed by other SCC
personnel to assist in the efficacy of SCC operations.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="tab-stops: -1.0in 0in"><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="tab-stops: -1.0in 0in"><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">&nbsp;</SPAN><U>FACTORS<o:p></o:p></U></P>
<P class=MsoNormal>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></P>
<P class=MsoNormal><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><U><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">Factor 1 - Knowledge Required by the
Position <o:p></o:p></SPAN></U></B></P>
<P class=MsoNormal><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><U><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">Knowledge</SPAN></U></B></P>
<P class=MsoNormal><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><U><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'"></SPAN></U></B><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">Comprehensive knowledge of the HHS
Response System, their organizational structures, operating procedures, safety
practices, terminology, and administration.</SPAN></P>
<P class=a
style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0in; TEXT-INDENT: 0in; tab-stops: -1.0in">Extensive
knowledge of the Federal Response Plan, particularly the ESFs that may apply to
HHS during a full activation of the Federal Response Plan (FRP) and other HHS
Memorandums of Understanding requiring HHS actions.</P>
<P class=a
style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0in; TEXT-INDENT: 0in; tab-stops: -1.0in">&nbsp;<SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">Knowledge of other disaster response
organizations and their missions (i.e. Federal Emergency Management Agency
(FEMA), Red Cross, National Transportation Safety Board (NTSB), Federal Bureau
of Investigation (FBI) and other Non-governmental Organizations
(NGOs).<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">&nbsp;</SPAN><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">Requires detailed knowledge of office
activities, procedures, techniques and practices in order to control and monitor
work assignments, shifting priorities as necessary to accomplish a smooth,
efficient work flow.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'"><o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>
<P class=a
style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0in; TEXT-INDENT: 0in; tab-stops: -1.0in">Comprehensive
knowledge of National Interagency Incident Management System/Incident Command
System (NIIMS/ICS).</P>
<H2><SPAN
style="FONT-WEIGHT: normal; FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial"><o:p></o:p></SPAN></H2>
<H3>Skills</H3>
<P class=MsoNormal>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></P>
<P class=MsoBodyText>Must be proficient in the advanced features of Word,
Powerpoint, Access and Excel.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
</SPAN>In-depth knowledge of database programs to include skills in performing
advanced queries, inputting and exporting data, implementing, documenting, and
maintaining database applications such as an incident log, personnel tracking,
etc.</P>
<P class=MsoNormal><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">Must be able to
assimilate large amounts of information from various sources into clear concise
reports, briefings and situational assessments.<SPAN
style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Must be able to synthesize divergent
information into an EOC Action Plan.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">&nbsp;</SPAN><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">Must have excellent Interpersonal skills;
the ability to interact with persons at all levels of government and civilian
agencies.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">Ability to
resolve adverse issues in a diplomatic manner to cause a positive reflection on
HHS supervisory and management skills that motivate employees to produce at the
highest output level for efficient operations in a stressful work
environment.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">&nbsp;</SPAN><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">Competent in the development and use of
integrated action planning concepts and processes.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>
<H2><SPAN
style="FONT-WEIGHT: normal; FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial">&nbsp;</SPAN>Abilities</H2>
<P class=MsoNormal>&nbsp;<SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">Ability to
assemble detailed information on operational situations, evaluate the
information to determine the rate of progress toward meeting established goals,
and present a document to management together with recommendations for
overcoming any problems identified. <o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">&nbsp;</SPAN><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">Ability to design, document and conduct
complex training programs and exercises that simulate tasks and scenarios likely
to be encountered during SCC activations.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'"><o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="tab-stops: -1.0in 0in"><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'"><SPAN
class=700480521-07012003>M</SPAN>ust be able to analyze a product to ensure it
interacts seamlessly with existing technology, significantly contributes to SCC
operations, and is capable of being successfully operated by intermittent
users.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">Ability to
communicate effectively, orally, and in writing, with managers and employees
within the government and emergency medical personnel outside the government who
are part of the State and local community.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">Ability to
effectively manage personnel, specialized equipment, and support resources
during a response situation.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
</SPAN>Ability to troubleshoot software applications and other electronics as
needed to support SCC operations.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">&nbsp;</SPAN><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">Ability to implement ICS principles
within the established Departmental guidelines.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'"><o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">Ability to
conduct briefings and planning meetings.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'"><o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">Ability to
manage response systems and activities, anticipate resource problems, and plan
the appropriate actions.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">&nbsp;</SPAN><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">Ability to motivate personnel and form
effective work groups.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">&nbsp;</SPAN><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">Ability to work with little or no
supervision.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal>&nbsp;</P>
<P class=MsoNormal><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><U><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">Factor 2 - Supervisory
Controls<o:p></o:p></SPAN></U></B></P>
<P class=MsoNormal><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">&nbsp;</SPAN><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">Work is performed under the very general
direction of the supervisor.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
</SPAN>Assignments are made in terms of broad objectives to be achieved.<SPAN
style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Within the accepted parameters of the
assignment, the incumbent is responsible for independent planning and organizing
work, coordinating with personnel inside and outside the Federal government, and
advising the supervisor of controversial findings, issues, or problems with
potential widespread impact.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
</SPAN>Completed work is reviewed in terms of overall effectiveness in achieving
intended objectives.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><U><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></U></B></P>
<H3>Factor 3 - Guidelines</H3>
<P class=MsoNormal><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><U><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></U></B></P>
<P class=MsoNormal><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">Guidelines
consist of general administrative policies, operating procedures, techniques,
practices, etc., which require considerable adaptation and/or interpretation for
application to issues and problems encountered.<SPAN
style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Administrative policies and precedent
provide a basic outline of results desired, but do not go into detail as to the
methods used to accomplish the work.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
</SPAN>The incumbent must use judgement and ingenuity in the development of
emergency response plans, strategies, and procedures.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><U><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">Factor 4 -
Complexity<o:p></o:p></SPAN></U></B></P>
<P class=MsoNormal><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><U><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></U></B></P>
<P class=MsoNormal><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">HHS is the lead
Federal agency for emergency preparedness in the health and medical services.
Work includes a broad range of activities related to the Department's overall
emergency preparedness program and within the Office of the Assistant Secretary
of Public Health Emergency Preparedness, its policies, plans, programs, and
operational activities.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Frequently,
the incumbent independently decides what needs to be done based on each
assignment, the outcome required, and the issues involved.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">The position
requires attention to step-by-step progression of a large number of separate
activities, and logistical planning to cause a number of unrelated actions to
happen at the proper time in the proper sequence.<SPAN
style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>The task is rendered much more difficult
by the fact that so much depends upon the coordination and cooperation of
various branches within OASPHEP and other agencies.<SPAN
style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>The tasks are further hampered by the
unpredictable nature, time and duration of activations.<SPAN
style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>In addition to causing actions to occur,
the position requires the ability to analyze what is happening, what if anything
is going wrong, and what to do about it.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
</SPAN>A high degree of analytical ability is needed to assess the situation and
respond accordingly.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>
<H1><U><SPAN
style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-size: 16.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial">Factor
5 - Scope and Effect<o:p></o:p></SPAN></U></H1>
<P class=MsoNormal>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="mso-pagination: lines-together"><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">The SCC is the focal point of information
released to the HHS community during response operations; it collects, analyzes,
synthesizes and reports all response operation activities.<SPAN
style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>In media sensitive events, the SCC
Director may work closely with OASPHEP management, HHS Public Affairs Officers,
and others to prepare press releases about an event.<SPAN
style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>The incumbent's performance has an
effect on the prestige and professional reputation of the OASPHEP.<SPAN
style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>A Top Secret will be required for the
position.</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="mso-pagination: lines-together"><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'"></SPAN><U><SPAN
style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-size: 16.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial">Factor
6 - Personal Contacts<o:p></o:p></SPAN></U></P>
<P class=MsoNormal>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></P>
<P class=MsoNormal><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">Incumbent
relates directly with the entire OASPHEP staff, agency personnel staff, Federal,
State and local government representatives, NDMS partner Federal agencies (DoD,
VA, and FEMA) and personnel from the NDMS teams. <o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal><SPAN
style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'"><o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>
<H1 style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><U><SPAN
style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-size: 16.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial">Factor
7 - Purpose of the Contacts</SPAN></U></H1>
<P class=MsoNormal><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">Contacts are to
discuss and coordinate technical issues, render advice and assistance, resolve
problems involving interrelationships of manpower needs in emergency
preparedness and response activities.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>
<H1><U><SPAN
style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-size: 16.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial">Factor
8 - Physical Demands</SPAN></U></H1>
<P class=MsoNormal><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'">Persons are
expected to be able to be CCRF fully qualified.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>
<H1><U><SPAN
style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-size: 16.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial">Factor
9 - Work Environment<o:p></o:p></SPAN></U></H1>
<P class=MsoNormal><SPAN
style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; LAYOUT-GRID-MODE: line; FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA">The
work is performed in an office setting with some travel to meetings,
conferences, and exercises.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>The
incumbent is responsible for activating the SCC.<SPAN
style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>The incumbent is required to work
irregular work schedules (evenings, nights, and weekends).Work may be subject to
tight deadlines and stressful conditions during emergency assignments.<SPAN
style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
</SPAN></SPAN><o:p></o:p></P></DIV></BODY></HTML>

